The paper discusses a technique to enhance the precision of analog-to-digital and digital-to-analog conversion, which is relevant to several subfields of computer science. The use of Monte Carlo methods suggests a focus on simulation and modeling, which is common in the subfield of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). The proposed technique may also have applications in the subfield of cs.EM (Electromagnetics), as it involves the spread of references' values into the neighbor sample space. The use of mathematical interpretation and the focus on precision enhancement suggests a connection to the subfield of cs.IT (Information Theory). The proposed technique may also have applications in the subfield of cs.SY (Systems and Control), as it involves improving the precision of biomedical information processing systems. Finally, the paper mentions an example of enhancing the precision of an implantable neurostimulator design, which suggests a connection to the subfield of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
